About the Role


   As part of the Operations unit within the Sustainalytics Corporate Solutions (SCS) team, the Data Analyst, Operations will support the global resourcing and operational efficiency of our Projects team in delivering licensed ESG ratings to corporate clients, second-party opinions to bond issuers, and additional related products. This unit is responsible for developing processes and tools which support the Projects team in scaling a growing portfolio of client deliverables in terms of both quantity, quality and timeliness. The volume of work and SCS Projects team size have grown by over 120% per year, requiring new approaches to scaling efficiency.
   The Data Analyst position covers a broad range of operational and quality management tasks; combining analytical, technical, and communication skills. The successful candidate will hit the ground running in our entrepreneurial environment by taking initiative on new responsibilities in order to quickly add value to our fast-growing team. Experience in data analytics, PowerApps, and data flow efficiency is beneficial in this role to maintain and enhance data storage and systems.



   Job Responsibilities


Design and maintain tracking and monitoring tools, combining data sources across internal platforms
Develop technical solutions and enhancements to improve efficiency and quality of client deliverables
Research and develop new business processes or data management systems to properly track and resource the delivery of our products
Collaborate with stakeholders to scope technical solutions and support operational activities including quality management, resource management and product management
Design KPI and tracking reports and support the delivery of monthly production and progress reports
Support upkeep and enhancement of existing data, systems and tools



   Qualifications


2-4 years of relevant technology or business process automation experience, including 2+ years of related technical business analysis, development or operations experience;
Degree(s) with focus on technology, engineering or business;
Fluency in English with strong communication skills that allow you to collaborate with stakeholders from multiple teams and at all levels;
Extensive experience in developing and using complex Excel workbooks, VBA for Excel, Power Automate, PowerApps, SQL and/or other data management tools;
Experience with, or willingness to learn, SharePoint, PowerBI, Microsoft Dynamics;
Experience in process automation or automated content creation considered an asset;
Experience with agile project management considered an asset;
Passion for sustainability and demonstrated interest and knowledge in the financial services industry and/or sustainable finance and green bonds an asset;
Flexible mindset; adaptable to a constantly shifting work environment;
Strong analytical skills and creative, problem-solving attitude;
Positive attitude, Innovative and entrepreneurial
Alignment with Sustainalytics’ mission, vision and values;



   About Us


   Sustainalytics is a Morningstar company dedicated to responsible investment with over 25 years' experience in ESG research and ratings. With an extensive client base across asset managers, asset owners and investment banks, our mission is to provide the insights required for investors and companies to make more informed decisions that lead to a more just and sustainable global economy.



   As Morningstar’s ESG center of excellence we are responsible for driving both the commercial success and innovation of its ESG products as well as its overall ESG strategy.



   In these times, we rely on virtual team meetings and management practices, as well as a remote buddy program, to support a smooth integration in our virtual offices. New team members are onboarded and start their first day with the company from the safety of their homes.



   For more information, visit 

   www.sustainalytics.com

As a Data Analyst at Behaviour, you will be responsible for the implementation and maintenance of effective tracking tools used for performance and quality reporting and analysis of assigned projects.




    As data expert on your project, you will be part of a multidisciplinary team, and your role will be to ensure analytical insight about challenges faced during the different phases of production.




In this role you will


 Develop telemetry during game production to ensure that player behaviour can be analysed;
 Identify, develop, and provide analytical answers to challenges faced by partners involved in game development;
 Develop optimized and clear output/outcome (dashboard reports and analyses) to meet the needs identified;
 Promote knowledge and understanding of player behaviour at studio level through clear and well-documented analyses;
 Establish strong working relationships with partners and colleagues built on trust and proximity;
 Work with different teams to adapt approaches and tools to solve complex problems and find good balance between velocity, accuracy, and quality.






What we're looking for


 2-3 years of experience in the field of analytics;
 Excellent knowledge of how to use databases, particularly complicated data processing of large data sets with SQL and NoSQL;
 Excellent data visualization skills (Power BI is a plus);
 Curious about what can be learned from data analysis;
 Autonomy and excellent organization skills;
 Thrive when faced with challenges and uncertainty.






Dans ce rôle, vous devrez


 Développer la télémétrie lors de la phase de production du jeu afin de s'assurer que le comportement des joueurs pourra être analysé ;
 Identifier, proposer et développer des réponses analytiques aux enjeux des partenaires impliqués sur un jeu ;
 Développer des sorties de résultats (tableaux de bords, rapports, analyses) optimisées et lisibles qui répondront aux besoins identifiés ;
 Promouvoir la connaissance et la compréhension des joueurs à travers la compagnie grâce à des analyses claires et documentées ;
 Nouer des relations fortes avec vos partenaires et collègues afin de travailler dans un contexte de confiance et proximité ;
 S’épanouir face au défi et à l'incertitude : en travaillant avec différentes équipes, vous devrez résoudre des problèmes, adapter votre approche et vos outils pour répondre à des questions complexes et trouver le juste équilibre entre rapidité, précision et qualité des différentes approches.






Ce que nous recherchons


 Sont essentiels :
 2-3 ans d'expérience dans un domaine analytique ;
 Excellentes compétences en manipulation de bases de données : traitement complexe de larges ensembles de données à l’aide de SQL, NoSQL ;
 Excellentes compétences en visualisation de données (Power BI est un atout) ;
 Curieux des enseignements à tirer des analyses de données ;
 Autonomie et sens aigu de l’organisation ;
 Bonnes compétences de communication ;
 Anglais courant ;
 Joueur d’équipe (l’humour est un atout).

 Sont des atouts :
 Compétences en programmation: une expérience avec Python / R ;
 Expérience des outils AWS et/ou Snowflake ;
 Expérience dans l’univers du jeu vidéo.






   En tant qu’Analyste de données chez Behaviour, vous êtes responsable de la mise en place et de la maintenance d’outils de suivi performants, vous permettant de produire des rapports et des analyses de qualité sur la performance des projets qui vous sont assignés.



 En tant qu’expert des données sur votre projet, vous travaillez au sein d’une équipe multidisciplinaire et avez pour rôle d’assurer une vision analytique sur les différents défis rencontrés lors de la production et la croissance d’un jeu vidéo.

